# Mode And Permission Discipline

## Purpose
Prevent workflow drift by enforcing strict behavior around active mode constraints and permission boundaries.

## Rules
- Respect the active mode as a hard boundary (Agent, Plan, Ask, Debug).
- Never request a mode switch unless the user explicitly asks for it or the current command explicitly requires consent to switch.
- If a mode switch is rejected, continue in the current mode without retrying or diverting the workflow.
- In Ask mode, use read-only actions only; do not edit files, run mutating commands, or perform commit operations.
- If a command requires write access but the current mode forbids it, explain the blocker clearly and ask for mode change before proceeding.
- Do not shift process burden to the user for agent-caused drift; recover by returning to the requested workflow immediately.

## Checklist
- [ ] Active mode identified before action.
- [ ] Mode-specific constraints respected.
- [ ] No unauthorized retries after rejected mode switch.
- [ ] Communication stays aligned with the requested command flow.

